    "narrative": "The LawDog lineup for April 10th is headlined by **Daulton Varsho** (72.16) and **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (71.61), who provide the safest floors and highest ceilings in today\u2019s slate. **Daulton Varsho** benefits from a strong matchup against Simeon Woods Richardson, buoyed by positive park factors and his ability to exploit the pitcher's hold percentage for stolen base potential. **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** remains our engine; while the dynamic platoon factor is slightly negative, his raw power profile against Bryce Elder makes him an automatic start in any format. **Jonathan Aranda** (70.47) and **Matt Chapman** (70.11) also crack the 70-point threshold, with **Jonathan Aranda** specifically benefiting from a massive +19% bump due to the favorable matchup against Luis Gil, and **Matt Chapman** enjoying a +16% park factor and high-efficiency steal potential against the slower delivery of Shane Baz.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was **Brendan Donovan** (59.16), who finished just shy of our 60-point threshold. While his +14% platoon edge against Tatsuya Imai made him a compelling candidate, he was edged out by the superior power-speed profiles of our primary outfielders. Our scoring is heavily influenced by today\u2019s \"Lineup Pending\" status; we have assumed favorable middle-of-the-order placement for **Will Smith**, **Cal Raleigh**, and **Tyler Freeman**, but any late-hour lineup adjustments could fluctuate these scores. Notably, **Taylor Ward** and **Jung Hoo Lee** are active despite some negative platoon-based degradation, as their park-adjusted projections and favorable matchups against Landen Roupp and Shane Baz, respectively, keep them well within the \"Strong\" start tier. Monitor the wind conditions for **Will Smith**, whose +5% wind boost at his home park is a marginal variable in an otherwise stable projection.",
